__________________________________________________________________ File:          A1. My First Filter__________________________________________________________________• Sample input text •Avenue du Général De Gaulle,à Strabourg.• Sample output text •Avenue du G&eacute;n&eacute;ral De Gaulle,&agrave; Strabourg.__________________________________________________________________ File:          DataBase(I)__________________________________________________________________Description:  Reformating database to an other format.See:          pattern, variable, bof/eof, macro.Use Macro:    "<word>"="[a-zA-Z, ]+"Note:         We put a CR in the bof/eof fields at the bof/eof pane of              filter preferences window.               • Sample input text •"be","was,were","been""buy","bought","bought"• Sample output text •Infinitif        = bePassé            = was,wereParticipe passé  = beenInfinitif        = buyPassé            = boughtParticipe passé  = bought__________________________________________________________________ File:          DataBase(II)__________________________________________________________________Description:  Reformating database to an other format.See:          pattern, variable with format, bof/eof, macro.Use Macro:    "<word>"="[a-zA-Z, ]+"Note:         We put a CR in the bof/eof fields at the bof/eof pane of              filter preferences window.               • Sample input text •"be","was,were","been""buy","bought","bought"• Sample output text (with spaces between two fields) •Infinitif   Passé       Participe passébe          was,were    been       buy         bought      bought  __________________________________________________________________ File:          DataBase(III)__________________________________________________________________Description:  Reformating database to an other format.See:          pattern, variable, bof/eof, macro.Use Macro:    "<word>"="[a-zA-Z, ]+"              • Sample input text •"be","was,were","been""buy","bought","bought"• Sample output text LIKES: (with tabulation between two fields) •Infinitif   Passé       Participe passébe          was,were    been       buy         bought      bought  __________________________________________________________________ File:          DateAtEOF__________________________________________________________________Description:  This filter add date to the end of file.See:          variable, bof/eof• Sample input text •     This is a input text.• Sample output text •     This is a small text.     Converted: Sun., Dec. 28, 1997__________________________________________________________________ File:          LinkURL__________________________________________________________________Description:  This filter add link to URL-like text.See:          macro, variable, regular expression.Use macro :   "<an>"="A-Za-z0-9_-"• Sample input text •  My home page is http://www.kagi.com/guoniu.   You can send me email at guoniu@kagi.com.   My old home page http://130.79.4.39/~guoniu/   is still valid.• Sample output text •  My home page is <a href="http://www.kagi.com/guoniu">http://www.kagi.com/guoniu</a>.   You can send me email at <a href="mailto::guoniu@kagi.com">guoniu@kagi.com</a>.   My old home page <a href="http://130.79.4.39/~guoniu/">http://130.79.4.39/~guoniu/</a>   is still valid.__________________________________________________________________ File:          MultiCononnes__________________________________________________________________Description:  This filter extracts one colonne for the             multi-colonnes text.See:          pattern, variable, pre/post.• Sample input text: (3 colonnes) •John relit     Just now the house is fairly     [col 3]la lettre      quiet. I am sitting in my room,  [col 3]          qu'il vient    and writing this letter to you.  [col 3]  d'écrire…      Mrs Young is in the kitchen.     [col 3]                 She is cooking lunch, and Helen  [col 3]                           is helping her.                  [col 3]  • Sample output text: (the 2nd colonne) •Just now the house is fairly    quiet. I am sitting in my room, and writing this letter to you. Mrs Young is in the kitchen.    She is cooking lunch, and Helen is helping her.                 __________________________________________________________________ File:          Word and Line (I)__________________________________________________________________Description:  Ajouter un mot en tete d'une ligne contenant             un mot precis (par exemple :"mot"):See:          macro<fr>, conditional find, pattern• Sample input text •je vais a la pechecette phrase contient des mots en certain nombrecette phrase contient un mot de trop• Sample output text •je vais a la pechecette phrase contient des mots en certain nombre{ENTETE}: cette phrase contient un mot de trop__________________________________________________________________ File:          Word and Line (II)__________________________________________________________________Description:  Supprimer une ligne contenant un certain mot             (par exemple "mot").See:          pattern, conditional find, macro• Sample input text •je vais a la pechecette phrase contient des mots en certain nombrecette phrase contient un mot de trop• Sample output text •je vais a la pechecette phrase contient des mots en certain nombre__________________________________________________________________ File:          Word and Line (III)__________________________________________________________________Description:  Supprimer toutes les lignes ne contenant pas un             certain mot (par exemple "mot").See:          pattern, conditional find, macro• Sample input text •je vais a la pechecette phrase contient des mots en certain nombrecette phrase contient un mot de trop• Sample output text •cette phrase contient un mot de trop__________________________________________________________________ File:          Write Fast Filter__________________________________________________________________Description:      The red char . represents all char, including CR.   It will search the whole input text.   If you want all char except CR, please use [^<r>].   It will search line by line, which is more fast.• Sample input text •###### Xyz, abdifidkfds fdksfdsjk fdslfjdsl fdkslfjdslj###### Xyz, abdifidkfds fdksfdsjk fdslfjdsl fdkslfjdslj###### Xyz, abdifidkfds fdksfdsjk fdslfjdsl fdkslfjdslj###### Xyz, abdifidkfds fdksfdsjk fdslfjdsl fdkslfjdslj###### Xyz, abdifidkfds fdksfdsjk fdslfjdsl fdkslfjdslj###### Xyz, abdifidkfds fdksfdsjk fdslfjdsl fdkslfjdslj###### Xyz, abdifidkfds fdksfdsjk fdslfjdsl fdkslfjdslj###### Xyz, abdifidkfds fdksfdsjk fdslfjdsl fdkslfjdslj__________________________________________________________________ EOF__________________________________________________________________